    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Db Performance sample code mistake: utilize a combination of {{vsprintf()}} and {{array_walk()}} to inject the values into the SQL</p>

<p><a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/performance.database.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>by the document, it show us the sample code like below :</p>

<p>{quote}
    // $adapter is the DB adapter. In Zend_Db_Table, retrieve
    // it using $this-&gt;getAdapter().
    $sql = vsprintf(
        self::SELECT_FOO,
        array_walk($values, array($adapter, 'quoteInto'))
    );
{quote}</p>

<p>but by the php manual, we know {{array_walk}} only return true or false .</p>

<p><a href="http://us.php.net/array_walk">http://us.php.net/array_walk</a>
<a href="http://us.php.net/vsprintf">http://us.php.net/vsprintf</a></p>

<p>so the {{vsprintf}} method did not return the right formatted sql as expected.</p>

